Cherry Street, east from Gouverneur Street, showing clearance created by the demolition of houses bearing Nos. 380 to 384, and 386 to 388, respectively on the N.W. and N.E. corners of Scammel Street.
March 22, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

Cherry Street, at the N.W. corner of Scammel Street. Also shown is a view northward on Scammel Street. This clearance was formed by the demolition of Nos. 380-384 Cherry Street, and Nos. 47-45 Scammel Street.

March 22, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
